summary:
5. Establish a UN Supervision Mission in Syria (UNSMIS) for 90 days, with up to 300 unarmed military observers and a civilian component.
Here is a clear and concise summary of the Security Council document:


2043 (2012)

The Security Council:

- Decides to establish a UN mission (UNSMIS) subject to assessment by the Secretary-General;

6. UNSMIS mandate is to monitor cessation of armed violence and support implementation of the Envoy's six-point proposal;

7. Requests Secretary-General and Syrian government to conclude a Status of Mission Agreement (SOMA) without delay;

8. Calls on Syrian government to facilitate UNSMIS operation, deployment, movement, access, communication, and interaction with individuals;

9. Calls on parties to guarantee UNSMIS personnel safety, with primary responsibility lying with Syrian authorities;

10. Requests Secretary-General to report on obstructions to UNSMIS operation;

11. Reiterates call for Syrian authorities to allow humanitarian access;

12. Invites Member States to contribute to UNSMIS;

13. Requests Secretary-General to report on implementation within 15 days and submit proposals for adjustments;

14. Intends to assess implementation and consider further steps;

15. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
